Bring a large #pot of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Add the @freekeh{3/4%cup} and continue to boil gently for ~{12%minutes}. Drain, cover with a #tea towel and keep to one side until everything else is ready.

Remove the core of the @red pepper{1}(chopped into small cubes ½ cm thick) and chop into small cubes ½ cm thick, if your knife skills allow. Finely slice the @spring onions{2}.

Make a dressing using the zest and juice of half the @lemon{1/2}(zested and juiced), @salt{1/4%tsp}, the @za'atar{1/2%tsp} spice and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Give it all a good whisk with a #whisk.

Mix the freekeh with the diced red pepper, spring onion, @pomegranate seeds{1} and half the dressing. Taste for seasoning and add more salt and pepper to your liking.

Divide the salad between your #bowls{} and top with @mint{3}(picked) leaves, @feta cheese{1}(crumbled) and a drizzle more of the dressing.